HEADWORD: Petit mal
<hw>Pe*tit" mal"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[F., lit., little
sickness.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The mildest form of epilepsy,
with momentary faintness or unconsciousness, but without convulsions; --
opposed to <contr>grand mal</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petitor</ent>⟦br⟧
